OL,3,CStarmer says state of prisons is
OL,4,C'worse' than he thought
OL,6,FThe automatic release point on
OL,7,Fstandard determinate sentences
OL,8,Fcurrently stands at 50% of the
OL,9,Fsentence, but could be reduced to 40%.
OL,11,FThose sentences do not cover the most
OL,12,Fserious cases like murder and rape,
OL,13,Fbut they do include other serious
OL,14,Fcrimes.
OL,16,FITV News' Deputy Political Editor
OL,17,FAnushka Asthana understands that
OL,18,FMahmood is likely to exclude two
OL,19,Fcategories if she goes ahead with the
OL,20,Freform: sex crimes and serious
OL,21,Fviolence.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
